'''益生菌'''（{{lang-en|Probiotics}}）是指一般認為食入後對[[宿主|宿主]]（如動物或人類）有正面效益的食入性[[微生物|微生物]]<ref>http://www.health.gov.tw/Default.aspx?tabid=417&mid=537&itemid=15622{{Dead link|date=2019年11月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref name="Expert">{{cite journal|last1=Hill|first1=C|last2=Guarner|first2=F|last3=Reid|first3=G|last4=Gibson|first4=GR|last5=Merenstein|first5=DJ|last6=Pot|first6=B|last7=Morelli|first7=L|last8=Canani|first8=RB|last9=Flint|first9=HJ|last10=Salminen|first10=S|last11=Calder|first11=PC|last12=Sanders|first12=ME|title=Expert consensus document. The International Scientific Association for Probiotics and Prebiotics consensus statement on the scope and appropriate use of the term probiotic.|journal=Nature Reviews. Gastroenterology & Hepatology|date=August 2014|volume=11|issue=8|pages=506–14|pmid=24912386|doi=10.1038/nrgastro.2014.66}}</ref><ref name=bridging>{{cite journal | vauthors = Rijkers GT, de Vos WM, Brummer RJ, Morelli L, Corthier G, Marteau P | title = Health benefits and health claims of probiotics: Bridging science and marketing | journal = British Journal of Nutrition | volume = 106 | issue = 9 | pages = 1291–6 | year = 2011 | url = https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/british-journal-of-nutrition/article/health-benefits-and-health-claims-of-probiotics-bridging-science-and-marketing/3C143B002B0289188B006FACA906E3BE/core-reader | pmid = 21861940 | doi = 10.1017/S000711451100287X | access-date = 2018-03-03 | archive-date = 2018-02-04 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180204124118/https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/british-journal-of-nutrition/article/health-benefits-and-health-claims-of-probiotics-bridging-science-and-marketing/3C143B002B0289188B006FACA906E3BE/core-reader | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

在醫學上，目前科學證據無法顯示益生菌的使用有助於改善[[免疫系統|免疫系統]]、改善腸道健康、緩解[[便秘|便秘]]及預防[[感冒|感冒]]等健康支持作用<ref name=bridging/><ref name=snake>{{cite journal | vauthors = Slashinski MJ, McCurdy SA, Achenbaum LS, Whitney SN, McGuire AL | title = "Snake-oil," "quack medicine," and "industrially cultured organisms:" biovalue and the commercialization of human microbiome research | journal = BMC Medical Ethics | volume = 13 | page = 28 | year = 2012 | pmid = 23110633 | pmc = 3512494 | doi = 10.1186/1472-6939-13-28}}</ref><ref name="fda">{{cite web | url=http://www.fda.gov/ICECI/EnforcementActions/WarningLetters/2011/ucm281492.htm | title=Warning letter to CocoKefir LLC | publisher=Compliance Branch, Inspections, Compliance, Enforcement, and Criminal Investigations, US Food and Drug Administration and Federal Trade Commission | date=22 November 2011 | accessdate=4 June 2016 | vauthors=Engle MK, Roosevelt MW, Waltrip EA | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://wayback.archive-it.org/7993/20161023100457/http://www.fda.gov/ICECI/EnforcementActions/WarningLetters/2011/ucm281492.htm | archivedate=2016年10月23日 | df= }}</ref>，美國[[聯邦貿易委員會|聯邦貿易委員會]]也不允許這類宣稱療效的廣告<ref name="ftc2010">{{cite web|title=Dannon Agrees to Drop Exaggerated Health Claims for Activia Yogurt and DanActive Dairy Drink FTC Charges that Evidence Supporting Benefits of Probiotics Falls Short|url=https://www.ftc.gov/news-events/press-releases/2010/12/dannon-agrees-drop-exaggerated-health-claims-activia-yogurt|publisher=Federal Trade Commission, US Government|accessdate=9 May 2017|date=15 December 2010|archive-date=2018-10-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181004071650/https://www.ftc.gov/news-events/press-releases/2010/12/dannon-agrees-drop-exaggerated-health-claims-activia-yogurt|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。英國[[國民保健署|國民保健署]]也不認為這些宣稱的療效有足夠的證據。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/probiotics/ |title=存档副本 |access-date=2021-03-24 |archive-date=2021-04-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210420102142/https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/probiotics/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

益生菌一般來說是安全的，但在極少數個案中可能造成細菌-宿主交互作用及[[不良反應|不良反應]]<ref name=DoronSnydman2015>{{cite journal | vauthors=Doron S, Snydman DR | title=Risk and safety of probiotics. | journal=Clin Infect Dis | year=2015 | volume=60 Suppl 2 | issue= | pages=S129-34 | pmid=25922398 | doi=10.1093/cid/civ085 | pmc=4490230 | url=http://cid.oxfordjournals.org/content/60/suppl_2/S129.long | type=Review | access-date=2018-03-03 | archive-date=2016-08-11 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160811145245/http://cid.oxfordjournals.org/content/60/suppl_2/S129.long | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=SinghiKumar2016>{{cite journal | vauthors=Singhi SC, Kumar S | title=Probiotics in critically ill children. | journal=F1000Res | year=2016 | volume=5 | pmid=27081478 | doi=10.12688/f1000research.7630.1 | pmc=4813632 | url=http://f1000research.com/articles/5-407/v1 | type=Review | pages=407 | access-date=2018-03-03 | archive-date=2018-08-24 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180824135203/https://f1000research.com/articles/5-407/v1 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=DurchscheinPetritsch2016>{{cite journal | vauthors=Durchschein F, Petritsch W, Hammer HF | title=Diet therapy for inflammatory bowel diseases: The established and the new. | journal=World J Gastroenterol | year=2016 | volume=22 | issue=7 | pages=2179–94 | pmid=26900283 | doi=10.3748/wjg.v22.i7.2179 | pmc=4734995 | url=http://www.wjgnet.com/1007-9327/full/v22/i7/2179.htm | type=Review | access-date=2018-03-03 | archive-date=2018-06-29 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180629074357/https://www.wjgnet.com/1007-9327/full/v22/i7/2179.htm | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

有研究人员认为若在抗生素治疗后服用益生菌会阻碍肠道微生物组的恢复。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cell.com/cell/fulltext/S0092-8674(18)31102-4 |title=Personalized Gut Mucosal Colonization Resistance to Empiric Probiotics Is Associated with Unique Host and Microbiome Features |access-date=2018-09-11 |archive-date=2021-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126022908/https://www.cell.com/cell/fulltext/S0092-8674(18)31102-4 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cell.com/cell/fulltext/S0092-8674(18)31108-5 |title=Post-Antibiotic Gut Mucosal Microbiome Reconstitution Is Impaired by Probiotics and Improved by Autologous FMT |access-date=2018-09-11 |archive-date=2020-05-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200514004420/https://www.cell.com/cell/fulltext/S0092-8674(18)31108-5 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==定義==
益生菌（Probiotics），源於[[希臘語|希臘語]]「for life」（對生命有益），中文譯為「益生菌」或「原生保健性菌種」；而益生菌主要是指[[乳酸菌|乳酸菌]]和[[益生酵母菌|部分酵母菌]]。

==歷史==
根據歷史記載，人類最早食用的益生菌來自於[[優酪乳|優酪乳]]。早在西元前3000多年前，居住在[[土耳其|土耳其]]高原的古代遊牧民族就已經製作和飲用優酪乳。最初的優酪乳可能起源於偶然。那時的存放方法落後，羊奶時常會變質，這是由於不良細菌污染羊奶，但是有一次空氣中優酪乳的乳酸菌偶然進入羊奶，這些益菌使羊奶發生類似於腸胃道內的變化，變得更為酸甜適口，這就是最早的酸奶。

西元前2000多年前，在[[希臘|希臘]]東北部和[[保加利亞|保加利亞]]地區生息的古代[[色雷斯人|色雷斯人]]也掌握製作優酪乳的技術。他們最初使用的也是羊奶。後來，優酪乳技術被古希臘人傳到歐洲的其他地方。

20世紀初，俄國科學家[[伊利亞·梅契尼可夫|伊利亞·梅契尼可夫]]（Élie Metchnikoff）在研究保加利亞人為何長壽者較多時，發現這些長壽者都愛喝優酪乳，而提出發酵後的乳類中所含的乳酸菌對人體健康有益的理論。

梅契尼可夫的研究成果使一位西班牙商人{{tsl|en|Isaac Carasso|艾薩克·卡拉索}}受到啟發，於1919年建立優酪乳製造廠（現今的[[達能集團|達能集團]]），把優酪乳當作一種具有藥物作用的「長壽飲料」放在藥房銷售。

==益生菌的食物==
益生元，又稱[[益生質|益生質]]、益菌生，就是益生菌的食物，通常是人類所不能消化，但是細菌卻可以從中提取養分（或者是促進生長的環境也算），益生質能夠促進腸胃道益生菌的繁衍。

==常見菌種==
一般所稱「乳酸菌」是指能利用碳水化合物進行發酵生產多量乳酸之細菌總稱，為一相當龐雜的菌群，近年來經由科技及分子生物學的不斷發展，目前普遍認為的乳酸菌已由早期的4個[[屬|屬]](genus)再細分及擴充為17個[[屬|屬]]273個[[種|種]](species)：

